articles.title: After Assad’s fall, some say it’s time for Syrian refugees to go home - The Washington Post
articles.description: A growing number of European countries said they would stop processing asylum claims, and some want to pressure Syrians to leave.
articles.content: The dramatic fall of former Syrian president Bashar al-Assad instantly intensified the debate across Europe and the Middle East over the worlds largest pool of refugees, with calls already accelerati… [+527 chars]
